    {
        "id": "comment_instructions",
        "type": "comment",
        "z": "tab_main",
        "name": "INSTRUCTIONS: Click buttons in order (1→2→3a→3b→4). Check Debug panel for results.",
        "info": "# Smart Bus Conductor Testing Flow\n\n## Order of Operations:\n1. **Create Test Trip** - Generates a passenger ticket\n2. **Test Disembark** - Simulates passenger exiting\n3a. **Bus Break - Going Out** - Passenger leaves during rest stop\n3b. **Bus Break - Coming In** - Passenger returns to bus\n4. **Get Active Trips** - Monitor active passengers (auto-refreshes every 10s)\n5. **Backend Health Check** - Verify backend is running\n\n## Requirements:\n- Backend must be running on http://localhost:8000\n- Run migrations: `python manage.py migrate`\n- Start server: `python manage.py runserver`\n\n## Notes:\n- Bus-break does NOT complete the trip (passenger still active)\n- Disembark COMPLETES the trip (passenger removed)\n- Create a new trip before each test scenario",
        "x": 380,
        "y": 20,
        "wires": []
    }
]
